  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bb0\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The consequences are going to be dire - Karu warned the President",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is imperative that an immediate solution to the political and economic crisis the country is currently facing is not delayed.",
        "In view of this, Karu Jayasuriya, the leader of the National Movement for Social Justice, has pointed out that it is necessary to bring about a very quick and practical political change in the country, and has accordingly urged President Gotabaya Rajapaksa to take steps to establish an all-party government that can win the trust of domestic and foreign organizations.",
        "Regarding the economic condition of the country and the measures to be taken by the government in this regard, Karu Jayasuriya, the leader of the National Movement for Social Justice and former speaker, has further said:",
        "Many days have passed since President Gotabaya Rajapaksa finally addressed the nation and pointed out a very important issue for the country.",
        "It is clear from the current actions that the President has not yet fulfilled the promise made during his speech.",
        "It can be clearly understood by the gap between the reforms expected by the government through the 22nd amendment to the constitution and the political and economic reforms demanded by the country's civil society organizations, political parties and social activists.",
        "Therefore, we request President Gotabaya Rajapaksa to immediately fulfill the promise he made during his speech to the nation on the 11th of May last month.",
        "Likewise, looking at the mutual difference between the goal that the government shows that can be achieved through the 22nd amendment to the constitution and the actual expectation of the people, we inform the president that we cannot rely on this.",
        "Accordingly, as an organization that acts responsibly considering the welfare of the country, we are never ready to give up our expectations and the actions to be taken through the political, economic and social reforms that need to be carried out in the country.",
        "At the same time, we request the leaders of all political parties and civil society activists in the country to insist on the re-implementation of the main issues contained in the 19th Amendment to the Constitution.",
        "And it is imperative to resolve the political and economic crisis the country is currently facing without any delay.",
        "In view of that, we emphasize that it is necessary to bring about a very quick and practical political change in the country, and we warn all parties that if it is not done, the country will face the worst possible destruction. Therefore, in the current situation, all political parties, both ruling and opposition, should realize their responsibility and come forward to act.",
        "In such a background, we urge the people to take steps to establish an all-party government that can win the trust of domestic and foreign organizations to find a suitable solution to the economic crisis that the countrymen are currently facing and envision a better future.",
        "Karu Jayasuriya emphasized in the report that we support the ideas presented by the Mahanayaka Theras and also request them to consider the suggestions made by intellectuals and labor organizations including the Sri Lankan Bar Association."
      ],
